<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US">
<head>
  <title>Brave UX - Work - WeddingWire</title>
  <%- include ../partials/_head %>
</head>
<body>
  <main class="wrapper case-study weddingwire">
    <header class="case-header">
      <div class="case-header-content container">
        <h5 class="case-header-client-name">WeddingWire</h5>
        <h1 class="case-header-tagline">One happy marriage.</h1>
        <h6 class="case-header-type">Uniﬁed Application Experience</h6>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="case-exec-summary padded">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="case-exec-summary-text">We provided a fresh perspective for WeddingWire’s design team to help take their world-class mobile and app UX to the next level.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-breakdown padded gray">
      <div class="container row between">
        <div class="case-breakdown-box column gutter">
          <p class="case-breakdown-heading">Challenge</p>
          <h3 class="case-breakdown-summary">
            Improve upon the best.
          </h3>
          <p class="case-breakdown-detail">
            To stay on top, WeddingWire engaged Brave UX to improve their industry-leading mobile website and family of apps.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="case-breakdown-box column gutter">
          <p class="case-breakdown-heading">Solution</p>
          <h3 class="case-breakdown-summary">
            Whiteboards &amp; ideas.
          </h3>
          <p class="case-breakdown-detail">
            Brave worked closely with WeddingWire’s talented design team to create a new navigation framework and tackle hard-hitting UX challenges.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="case-breakdown-box column gutter">
          <p class="case-breakdown-heading">Scope</p>
          <ul class="case-breakdown-list">
            <li class="case-breakdown-list-item">UX Consulting</li>
            <li class="case-breakdown-list-item">Information Architecture</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block row">
      <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md padded column half-md">
        <div class="inner-block-content container">
          <h2 class="case-block-heading">Sort, simplify, &amp; select.</h2>
          <p class="case-block-text">
            As brides and grooms sort through vendors, we simplified decision-making (more than just the number of clicks) to prevent decision-fatigue across over 150 data points. This simplifies user decision-making (rather than simply the number of clicks) to prevent users’ decision-fatigue.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="inner-block column half-md hide-overflow dark-blue weddingwire-wireframe">
        <img src="./images/work/weddingwire/wireframe.svg " alt="" class="inner-block-image sr-bottom">
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block padded blue">
      <div class="row container">
        <div class="inner-block column half-md two-third-lg half-xl weddingwire-devices">
          <img src="./images/work/weddingwire/devices-bg.svg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
          <div class="frame frame-mobile-ios darker sr-top absolute-bottom">
            <div class="frame-container">
                <img src="./images/work/weddingwire/devices-left.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image">
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="frame frame-mobile darker sr-bottom absolute-bottom">
            <div class="frame-container">
                <img src="./images/work/weddingwire/devices-right.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image">
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md order-top-xs gutter-bottom-mobile column half-md one-third-lg half-xl">
          <div class="inner-block-content gutter-left">
            <h2 class="case-block-heading">Know thy user.</h2>
            <p class="case-block-text">
              Brave created user personas to better understand mobile users, their unique needs, and likely use cases. We then reviewed, validated, and refined WeddingWire’s existing prototypes to ensure the UX delivered.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block padded-top">
      <div class="row container">
        <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md column half-md two-third-lg">
          <div class="inner-block-content gutter-right padded-bottom">
            <h2 class="case-block-heading">What does 4.9 stars mean?</h2>
            <p class="case-block-text">
              We normalized data from reviews to make it more meaningful to users, so they can make more informed decisions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="inner-block column half-md one-third-lg">
            <img src="./images/work/weddingwire/phone.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain sr-bottom">
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block">
      <img src="./images/work/weddingwire/bouquet.jpg" alt="" class="block-image">
    </section>

    <section class="case-referral centered row">
      <div class="inner-block padded column gray">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="case-referral-quote-icon"></div>
          <p class="case-referral-text centered">&ldquo;Brave’s partnership served as a great sounding board and provided our team with valuable support to further elevate the WeddingWire mobile apps and mobile UX. Their understanding of UX is absolutely first-class.&rdquo;</p>
          <p class="case-referral-author">Sonny Ganguly, <em>CMO, WeddingWire</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <%- include ../partials/_footer-scripts %>

</body>
</html>
